shell.c

An basic shell progrm written in c. Using skeleton code from blackboard.

Support Features:

1.Support basic command: cd exit jobs fg bg.
2.Support terminal control and foreground, background process. 
	a)To stop foreground process, use ctrl-z. 
	b)To terminate foreground process, use ctrl-c.
	c)To change backgound process (included stopped process) 
	  to foreground proess, use fg <jobid> .
	d)To change stopped process to background, use bg <jobid> .
	e)Running statment in backgound, use '&' in the end.
3.Support pipe, by using '|'.
	a)Pipe only support last statment in background.
	b)Pipe support terminal control.
